  "prompt": "Has anyone ever died and then revived? What did they see when they die?",
  "response": "There have been many reported near-death experiences (NDEs) where people claim to have been clinically dead for a short time and then revived. While these experiences vary, some common themes include:\n\n1. Seeing a bright light\n2. Feeling a sense of peace\n3. Experiencing a tunnel-like sensation\n4. Encountering deceased relatives\n5. Feeling out of body\n\nHowever, scientific explanations suggest these experiences may be the result of:\n- Oxygen deprivation to the brain\n- Release of endorphins\n- Hallucinations caused by brain chemistry changes\n\nNo definitive scientific proof exists that consciousness continues after death. Each account is subjective and cannot be independently verified. Medical professionals continue to study near-death experiences to understand brain function during extreme conditions.",
